title: For Sale:  Makarov Semi-Automatic Service Pistol - East German manufacture
postcontent:
East German Makarov with holster and two (2) magazines.
Excellent condition with normal service pistol wear.
Nice shooter. Has the very good East German trigger.
Makes an excellent concealed carry pistol since it is compact, extremely rugged and reliable.

When I bought the pistol, it did not fire reliably; so I disassembled it, thoroughly cleaned it, and replaced the firing pin, main spring and recoil spring while I had it disassembled.
The firing problem was just a very dirty firing pin channel (probably never cleaned), but I replaced the firing pin anyway since I had a new one.
Upgraded the recoil spring to a 19lb Extra Power Wolff spring as recommended at the time by Makarov.com.
Original plastic grips have been replaced with very comfortable Pearce Rubber grips.
Operates perfectly since reassembly. About 300 rounds through it with no problems using inexpensive Russian factory ammo.


Here are some links to Makarov Pistol Info in case you are not very familiar with the Makarov -- pronounced  'ma KAR ov'  (think Russian)

http://www.makarov.com/
http://www.makarov.com/makfaq.html

Makarov Variant Shootoff 
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=etZYLLhLGdg

The Pistolet Makarova was designed by Russian: Nikolai Federovich Makarov. The design was for a simple and reliable, medium-power pistol to be used as the sidearm of the Soviet Forces. Accepted by the Russian military in 1951, it became the Soviet Union's standard military side arm from 1951-1991. As of 2012, large numbers of Makarov PMs are still in Russian military and police service; and the Makarov is still the service pistol of many Eastern European and former Soviet republics. China, North Korea and Vietnam also use Makarov PMs as standard-issue pistols.

The 5 countries that produced the Makarov:
    Russia - home of Nikolai Federovich Makarov
    East Germany - The Ernst Thaelman Factory
    China
    Bulgaria - The Arsenal Factory and Miltex
    Germany (post-unification) - The Simson Suhl

The Ernst Thaelman factory in Suhl,Thueringen made what are generally considered the finest Makarovs produced before the Berlin wall fell. The finish is nicely blued, with the high quality fit and machining you would expect from German craftmanship, and they are great shooters with a very good trigger. Most imported into this country were former service pistols, so their condition varies; but most have more holster wear than bore wear. If you want a nice shooter, the East German are the ones to buy.

title: For Sale:  Has the whole gun community lost it's collective mind?
postcontent:
We are supposed  to be Brothers in Arms not a bunch money hungry gougers! The prices people are asking and paying for firearms and ammo is insane! The government  hasn"t made any laws, they are just proposing them.  What is going to happen if they actually do enact any gun control  legislation? 

I understand supply and demand.  I also know quite a few FFL's and yes distributors are out of stock of almost everything!  However the distributors nor the manufacturers have raised their prices nor do they intent to! Has Walmart, Academy, Bass Pro or Cabela's  raised their prices?  No they haven't.  It is the individual seller and the small retailer that is screwing all of us!  It is the same thing that we all bitch about when we feel that Wall Street,  the oil IN companies and big business are sticking it to us. 

It is time for all of us to band together and invite others to join us,  the NRA,  Gun Owner's of America and other pro-gun organizations in stopping the government from making our sport something that only the wealthy can enjoy!

title: For Sale/Trade:  1960 Thompson Sea-Lancer 17' Vintage Wooden Boat for sale or trade
postcontent: I have decided it's time to sell my 1960 Thompson Sea-Lancer Runabout. I will consider trading for hand guns and/or high powered rifles. Make me an offer. I am ready to sell. This boat has been restored & maintained and in my opinion is in very good condition. I purchased the it partially restored from the third owner. It was given to him by his father in law who purchased it from the original owner. This is the original package as it was when it rolled off the dealers showroom floor 52 years ago. The hull was built by Thompson Bros. Boat Mfg. in Peshtigo, WI. in late 1960 and sold to a dealership in Chicago in early 1961. The dealership then fitted it with the motor and assigned a trailer. The motor is a 1961 Evinrude Starflite III with the 20 amp unicharger. Everything works. This motor was state of the art in 1961. In fact, this exact model was used in March of 1960 to set the world speed record on Lake Havasu of 114.6 miles per hour. This motor has been completely gone through and runs like a top. The cylinders have all been honed out and fitted with brand new piston rings. We installed a brand new impeller and replaced every single gasket from top to bottom end. There were a few dings on the hood that we fixed, too. The trailer is a 1961 Tee Nee OB-1300A tilt trailer made in Youngstown, Ohio. I repainted it from ground up with a slightly brighter yellow than Tee Nee used. I just thought this brighter shade made the trailer pop. It still has the original tear drop fenders and believe it or not, the tilt still works perfectly. As far as extra are concerned, we bought about $3000.00 in new custom cushions and custom canvas. The original boats in those days did not have cushions. Just nice comfortable hard wood benches. We had to upgrade that. We also installed a stereo system with 4 speaker strategically mounted so not to damage or even modify the original structure. We also installed new marine grade carpet on all the floordecking. The inside of the hull is sealed. Since we bought the boat it has always been in stored hanging in a garage during the winter months. We generally pull the motor off in October and store it on a motor stand in a heated work shop after winterizing it. All of the accessories that I have will go with the boat. Including a spare motor if you want it. It is in pieces, but the buyer is welcome to it. Also, included will be 6 life jackets, a knee board, a set of original Thompson Bros. wooden combo skis, 2 metal gas cans, 1 plastic gas can, manual for the motor, parts list for the motor, ski ropes, first aid kit, fire ex.,new wooden oars, 1 spare prop w/hardware, a 10 lbs. anchor, a Thompson Bros. flag and anything else I can find that goes with it. Whoever gets this boat won't be disappointed. It is a real head turner that everyone wants to know about. If would like to inspect the boat please contact me to make arrangements. The boat will be given over to it's new owner when the agreed upon amount is paid in cash or by credit card. We accept Visa, MasterCard, Discover and Americam Express, All information is from memory, buyer to verify all information. Ask questions. I have tons of photos. If you want to see more just let me know and I will send them.

title: For Sale:  FA 91 (H&K G3 Clone) Super Clean, Like New - Credit Cards Accepted $999.00
postcontent:
This rifle is MADE IN THE USA!  No Chinese junk here!  

The Good:  This is a powerful battle rifle in .308 that is a US made clone of the German G3 military rifle.  It comes with (4) 20 round magazines and the great news is that buying more magazines is cheep and easy.  Of all the military rifles in civilian use (AR-15, M1A, Mini-14, etc.) the G3/CETME/FA91 mags are by FAR the cheapest.  If you are a prepper and want 60 fully loaded mags in your basement this is an ideal way to go.  At 400 yards and in, it is as good as any rack military rifle (that is not one that has hundreds of dollars of gun smithing work or more).  If you are not  familiar with shooting, 400 yards is long shoot and is the outer limits of range with any rifle for the average citizen that does not practice by shooting 800 to 1000 rounds per year.

The Bad:  No, you are not going to go to Camp Perry and win the 1000 yard service rifle competition this August with this rifle.  You will need a $4,000+ rifle and the time and money for lots of practice for that.  Also, the G3's are notorious for hard charging (pulling the bolt back to make the rifle ready to fire the first round).  Every five to ten thousand thousand rounds, you will need to check the head spacing as is the case will pretty much all G3/CETME/FA91 designs.  

About the Seller:  I am a licensed attorney and long time advocate of gun rights.  We have a right from God to self defense.  The Constitution of the United States and that of Ohio provides political protection and recognition of these rights.  The second amendment has nothing to do with hunting, it is there to protect us from the number 1 mass murderer in all of history - tyrannical government.  Thus, every responsible family leader really should have at least one decent military rifle.  

Terms of sale:  All transactions will take place face to face in my law office in Delaware, Ohio.  You must be a resident of Ohio and not have any prohibition limiting your ability to purchase and own this rifle. Valid driver's license is required, valid Concealed Carry license preferred.  I do not make copies of this information as I will respect your privacy.  Credit Card transactions are subject to a 3% additional charge (this is a pass along cost).

title: For Sale/Trade:  Custom 2001 SAR3 AK
postcontent:
Custom 2001 SAR3, 5.56 AK for sale. The factory trigger assembly was replaced with the Red Star Arms fire control group which includes an adjustable trigger - the user can adjust it - and a properly configured hammer for the SAR-3. The factory hammer was known to cause uneven wear on the bolt in these rifles and they also suffered from trigger slap, so this is and incredibly important upgrade on the SAR3. The original FSB was replaced with an original Romanian threaded 22mm front sight base and a US-made copy of the Romanian muzzlebrake by AK-USA. All parts were installed by Troy at InRange in Kodak, Tennessee. Troy installed everything and then parkerized and painted the rifle. I don't think anyone interested in AKs can question the high quality of Troy's work. The finish is smooth, even, and looks phenomenal, especially compared to other AKs. The muzzlebrake and FSB are fully functional as designed (plunger and spring to lock the brake in place upon tightening) and the muzzlebrake is fully removable. The furniture is laminated wood from Russia with the exception of the laminated repo handgrip which is US made. The furniture was professionally refinished with an authentic Russian look, Includes two 30 round waffle mags.

FIRST $1,000 TAKES IT! But that offer is only open for the next couple weeks.
